## 📊 Data Flow Architecture

```
PHASE 1 (Complete):
Config → StrategyConfig (Pydantic) → ConstraintValidator → Valid/Invalid
HTML Report → ReportParser → BacktestResult → Metrics Calculated

PHASE 2 (Planned):
Database (PostgreSQL) ← Store all results
ConstraintValidator ← Hard rules
ResultAnalyzerAgent → Identify weaknesses (via llama3.2:3b)
StrategyImproverAgent → Propose changes

PHASE 3 (Planned):
Templates (Jinja2) + Config → CodeGeneratorAgent (qwen2.5-coder:7b) → MQL5
ConstraintValidator → Valid code only

PHASE 4 (Planned):
Orchestrator → [Generate → Validate → Write] → [MT5 Backtest] → [Parse → Analyze → Improve]
Loop until: Strategy meets all 4 targets OR max iterations reached

PHASE 5 (Planned):
Database → Correlation Analysis
Champion System → Best performers
Multi-pair → EURUSD + GBPUSD + USDJPY
Walk-forward → Out-of-sample validation
Export → CSV/Excel reports
```

